The European internal market is one of the most important achievements in the process of integrating Europe .
Only a well-functioning internal market will be able to guarantee the competitive environment required for entrepreneurship and contribute to the development of the European economy .
The Internal Market Scoreboard is a tool for monitoring the introduction , proper transposition and application of directives on the internal market .
The analysis of the data contained in the Internal Market Scoreboard provides an exceptionally interesting information on the work done by the Member States in the introduction of European Union legislation .
This is a typical political instrument , but it should not be easy ; it should act as a means encouraging the legislation of responsible individuals more quickly and more correct .
This applies especially to the new Member States , where no legislation was able to meet the objectives set out by state or governments .
Furthermore , the Scoreboard of the internal market should be used more frequently in discussions on the status of the internal market .
It is therefore necessary to develop a more form of available to the Scoreboard , which could also be used by citizens who are interested in issues related to the internal market .
The rapporteur pointed out that some directives , such as the Services Directive , are other important for the effective functioning of the internal market .
I agree with the rapporteur on this issue , and I therefore believe that the Commission should take into account indicators that reflect better the direct importance of directives for businesses and citizens .
